---
import PageLayout from '../../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import HeroSection from '../../components/widgets/Hero.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';

const meta = {
  title: "Complete Guide to Waterproofing Materials & DIY Sump Pump Installation",
  description: "Learn about liquid membranes (Aquablock), dimpled membranes (Delta MS), French drains, and complete DIY sump pump installation with concrete mixing guide.",
  keywords: "waterproofing materials, Aquablock, Delta MS, French drain, sump pump installation, DIY waterproofing, concrete mixing, Liberty pump",
  canonical: "https://dryspacewaterproofing.ca/blog/waterproofing-materials-sump-pump-diy-guide"
};
---

<PageLayout {...meta}>
  
  <!-- Breadcrumbs -->
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4 mt-4">
    <Breadcrumbs 
      items={[
        { name: "Home", url: "/" },
        { name: "Blog", url: "/blog" },
        { name: "Waterproofing Materials Sump Pump Diy Guide" }
      ]}
    />
  </div>

<HeroSection
    title="Waterproofing Materials & DIY Sump Pump Guide"
    subtitle="Everything You Need to Know About Modern Waterproofing Systems"
    backgroundImage="/images/waterproofing-materials.webp"
    ctaText="Get Professional Help"
    ctaLink="/free-inspection"
  />

  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
      <!-- Introduction -->
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none mb-12">
        <p class="text-xl text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-8">
          Understanding waterproofing materials is crucial for protecting your home from water damage. This comprehensive guide covers professional-grade materials from liquid membranes to drainage systems, plus a complete DIY guide for sump pump installation including proper concrete mixing techniques.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Part 1: Waterproofing Materials -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8 text-slate-900 border-b-4 border-cyan-600 pb-4">
          Part 1: Professional Waterproofing Materials Explained
        </h2>

        <!-- Liquid Waterproofing Membrane - Aquablock -->
        <div class="bg-cyan-50 rounded-lg p-8 mb-8">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Liquid Waterproofing Membrane: Aquablock 720-38</h3>
          
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-6">
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold mb-3">What is Aquablock?</h4>
              <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4">
                Aquablock 720-38 is a rubberized asphalt emulsion that creates a seamless, flexible waterproof barrier when applied to foundation walls. It cures to form a thick, rubber-like membrane that bridges cracks and resists water penetration.
              </p>
              
              <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-4">
                <h5 class="font-semibold mb-2">Key Properties:</h5>
                <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
                  <li>• Seamless application (no joints)</li>
                  <li>• Self-healing for minor cracks</li>
                  <li>• Elongation: 1,200%</li>
                  <li>• Thickness: 60 mils when dry</li>
                  <li>• VOC compliant</li>
                  <li>• Cold applied (no heating)</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold mb-3">Application Process</h4>
              <div class="space-y-3">
                <div class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="bg-cyan-600 text-white rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-3 flex-shrink-0">1</span>
                  <div>
                    <strong>Surface Preparation</strong>
                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">Clean wall, repair major cracks, ensure dry surface</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="bg-cyan-600 text-white rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-3 flex-shrink-0">2</span>
                  <div>
                    <strong>Primer Application</strong>
                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">Apply Aquablock primer at 200-300 sq ft/gallon</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="bg-cyan-600 text-white rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-3 flex-shrink-0">3</span>
                  <div>
                    <strong>Spray or Trowel</strong>
                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">Apply 2 coats at 1.5 gallons per 100 sq ft</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="bg-cyan-600 text-white rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-3 flex-shrink-0">4</span>
                  <div>
                    <strong>Protection Board</strong>
                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">Install drainage board over membrane</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-cyan-50 rounded-lg p-4 mt-6">
            <p class="text-sm">
              <strong>Cost:</strong> $3-5 per sq ft installed | <strong>Lifespan:</strong> 20-30 years | <strong>Best for:</strong> New construction and full excavation repairs
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Dimpled Waterproofing Membrane - Delta MS -->
        <div class="bg-cyan-50 rounded-lg p-8 mb-8">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Dimpled Membrane: Delta-MS</h3>
          
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-6">
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold mb-3">What is Delta-MS?</h4>
              <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4">
                Delta-MS is a high-density polyethylene (HDPE) dimpled sheet that creates an air gap between the foundation wall and soil. The dimples face the wall, creating drainage channels that direct water down to the weeping tile system.
              </p>
              
              <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-4">
                <h5 class="font-semibold mb-2">Technical Specifications:</h5>
                <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
                  <li>• Dimple height: 5/16" (8mm)</li>
                  <li>• Material: Virgin HDPE</li>
                  <li>• Compressive strength: 5,200 psf</li>
                  <li>• Roll size: 6.5' x 65.6' (426 sq ft)</li>
                  <li>• Air gap volume: 0.23 gallons/sq ft</li>
                  <li>• UV resistant for 6 months</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold mb-3">Installation Method</h4>
              <div class="space-y-3">
                <div class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="bg-cyan-600 text-white rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-3 flex-shrink-0">1</span>
                  <div>
                    <strong>Wall Preparation</strong>
                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">Clean wall, apply sealant to cracks</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="bg-cyan-600 text-white rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-3 flex-shrink-0">2</span>
                  <div>
                    <strong>Molding Strip</strong>
                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">Install termination bar at top of wall</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="bg-cyan-600 text-white rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-3 flex-shrink-0">3</span>
                  <div>
                    <strong>Sheet Installation</strong>
                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">Dimples facing wall, overlap 6 inches</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="bg-cyan-600 text-white rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-3 flex-shrink-0">4</span>
                  <div>
                    <strong>Secure & Seal</strong>
                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">Fasten with washers, seal overlaps</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mt-6">
            <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-4">
              <h5 class="font-semibold mb-2 text-cyan-700">Advantages</h5>
              <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
                <li>✓ Creates air gap for ventilation</li>
                <li>✓ Bridges wall irregularities</li>
                <li>✓ Protects waterproofing during backfill</li>
                <li>✓ Can be installed in any weather</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-4">
              <h5 class="font-semibold mb-2 text-orange-700">Limitations</h5>
              <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
                <li>✗ Not a waterproofing (drainage only)</li>
                <li>✗ Requires proper weeping tile</li>
                <li>✗ Can't seal active leaks</li>
                <li>✗ Visible seams between sheets</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-cyan-50 rounded-lg p-4 mt-4">
            <p class="text-sm">
              <strong>Cost:</strong> $1.50-2.50 per sq ft installed | <strong>Lifespan:</strong> 50+ years | <strong>Best for:</strong> Drainage improvement and protection layer
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- French Drain System -->
        <div class="bg-orange-50 rounded-lg p-8 mb-8">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">French Drain System Components</h3>
          
          <div class="mb-6">
            <h4 class="font-bold mb-4">1. Perforated Drain Pipe with Mesh Sock</h4>
            
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
              <div>
                <h5 class="font-semibold mb-2">Big 'O' Perforated Pipe</h5>
                <ul class="text-sm space-y-2">
                  <li>• <strong>Size:</strong> 4" diameter standard</li>
                  <li>• <strong>Material:</strong> Corrugated HDPE</li>
                  <li>• <strong>Perforation:</strong> 2 rows of 5/8" holes</li>
                  <li>• <strong>Spacing:</strong> Holes at 120° apart</li>
                  <li>• <strong>Flow rate:</strong> 20 GPM per 100 ft</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              
              <div>
                <h5 class="font-semibold mb-2">Filter Sock Purpose</h5>
                <ul class="text-sm space-y-2">
                  <li>• <strong>Material:</strong> Non-woven geotextile</li>
                  <li>• <strong>Weight:</strong> 4 oz/sq yard</li>
                  <li>• <strong>Function:</strong> Prevents soil infiltration</li>
                  <li>• <strong>Permeability:</strong> 100 gallons/min/sq ft</li>
                  <li>• <strong>Life:</strong> 20+ years underground</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="bg-amber-50 rounded-lg p-4 mt-4">
              <p class="text-sm font-semibold">
                ⚠️ CRITICAL: Holes must face DOWN (at 4 and 8 o'clock positions) to prevent sediment entry
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-bold mb-4">2. 3/4" Clear Gravel Drainage Bed</h4>
            
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
              <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-4">
                <h5 class="font-semibold mb-2">Specifications</h5>
                <ul class="text-xs space-y-1">
                  <li>• Size: 3/4" (19mm)</li>
                  <li>• Type: Clear stone</li>
                  <li>• No fines/dust</li>
                  <li>• Angular preferred</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              
              <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-4">
                <h5 class="font-semibold mb-2">Installation</h5>
                <ul class="text-xs space-y-1">
                  <li>• 6" below pipe</li>
                  <li>• 6" above pipe</li>
                  <li>• 12" wide minimum</li>
                  <li>• Wrapped in fabric</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              
              <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-4">
                <h5 class="font-semibold mb-2">Volume Calc</h5>
                <ul class="text-xs space-y-1">
                  <li>• 1 cubic yard = 27 cu ft</li>
                  <li>• Covers 27 sq ft at 12"</li>
                  <li>• Weight: 1.3 tons/yard</li>
                  <li>• Order 10% extra</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Sump Pump System -->
        <div class="bg-purple-50 rounded-lg p-8 mb-8">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Sump Pump System: Liberty 237 (1/3 HP)</h3>
          
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold mb-3">Liberty 237 Specifications</h4>
              <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-4">
                <ul class="text-sm space-y-2">
                  <li>• <strong>Power:</strong> 1/3 HP</li>
                  <li>• <strong>Flow:</strong> 2,400 GPH at 5 ft head</li>
                  <li>• <strong>Max head:</strong> 20 feet</li>
                  <li>• <strong>Discharge:</strong> 1-1/2" NPT</li>
                  <li>• <strong>Solids handling:</strong> 3/8"</li>
                  <li>• <strong>Switch type:</strong> VMF (wide angle)</li>
                  <li>• <strong>Housing:</strong> Thermoplastic</li>
                  <li>• <strong>Warranty:</strong> 3 years</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              
              <div class="mt-4 p-3 bg-cyan-50 rounded-lg">
                <p class="text-sm">
                  <strong>Why Liberty 237?</strong> Reliable, affordable, handles most residential applications, readily available parts
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold mb-3">Backwater Valve for Discharge</h4>
              <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-4">
                <h5 class="font-semibold mb-2">Purpose & Installation</h5>
                <ul class="text-sm space-y-2">
                  <li>• Prevents water backflow into pit</li>
                  <li>• Install vertically above pump</li>
                  <li>• Use union fitting for service</li>
                  <li>• Spring-loaded flapper design</li>
                  <li>• Clear body to monitor operation</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              
              <div class="mt-4 p-3 bg-amber-50 rounded-lg">
                <p class="text-sm">
                  <strong>Note:</strong> Some municipalities require backwater valve installation by code
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="mt-6 bg-cyan-50 rounded-lg p-4">
            <h5 class="font-bold mb-2">Pump Performance Chart</h5>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-4 gap-2 text-sm">
              <div class="font-semibold">Head (ft)</div>
              <div class="font-semibold">5'</div>
              <div class="font-semibold">10'</div>
              <div class="font-semibold">15'</div>
              <div class="font-semibold">Flow (GPH)</div>
              <div>2,400</div>
              <div>1,980</div>
              <div>1,440</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Part 2: DIY Sump Pump Installation -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8 text-slate-900 border-b-4 border-red-600 pb-4">
          Part 2: Complete DIY Sump Pump Installation Guide
        </h2>

        <!-- Critical Requirements -->
        <div class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-600 rounded-lg p-8 mb-8">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6 text-red-900">Critical Requirements - DO NOT SKIP</h3>
          
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold mb-3">MUST Use Black ABS Pipe</h4>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
                <li class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="text-red-600 mr-2">⚠️</span>
                  <span><strong>Black ABS only</strong> - Required by code</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="text-red-600 mr-2">⚠️</span>
                  <span><strong>Never use white PVC</strong> - Will fail</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="text-red-600 mr-2">⚠️</span>
                  <span><strong>1-1/2" minimum diameter</strong></span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="text-red-600 mr-2">⚠️</span>
                  <span><strong>Schedule 40 thickness</strong></span>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold mb-3">MUST Use Yellow ABS Glue</h4>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
                <li class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="text-amber-600 mr-2">⚠️</span>
                  <span><strong>Yellow ABS cement only</strong></span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="text-amber-600 mr-2">⚠️</span>
                  <span><strong>Not clear PVC glue</strong> - Won't bond</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="text-amber-600 mr-2">⚠️</span>
                  <span><strong>Apply to both surfaces</strong></span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="text-amber-600 mr-2">⚠️</span>
                  <span><strong>Work fast - 30 second working time</strong></span>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Step-by-Step Installation -->
        <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-lg p-8 mb-8">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Step-by-Step Sump Pump Installation</h3>
          
          <!-- Step 1: Excavation -->
          <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-6 mb-4">
            <h4 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-700">Step 1: Pit Excavation</h4>
            
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
              <div>
                <h5 class="font-semibold mb-2">Pit Dimensions</h5>
                <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
                  <li>• <strong>Width:</strong> 24 inches minimum</li>
                  <li>• <strong>Depth:</strong> 30 inches minimum</li>
                  <li>• <strong>Shape:</strong> Round or square</li>
                  <li>• <strong>Location:</strong> Lowest corner of basement</li>
                  <li>• <strong>From wall:</strong> 8-12 inches minimum</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              
              <div>
                <h5 class="font-semibold mb-2">Basin Selection</h5>
                <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
                  <li>• <strong>Size:</strong> 18" diameter x 22" deep</li>
                  <li>• <strong>Material:</strong> Polyethylene or polypropylene</li>
                  <li>• <strong>Perforations:</strong> Yes for groundwater</li>
                  <li>• <strong>Sealed lid:</strong> Required by code</li>
                  <li>• <strong>Capacity:</strong> 15-25 gallons</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Step 2: Discharge Line -->
          <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-6 mb-4">
            <h4 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-700">Step 2: Discharge Line Installation</h4>
            
            <div class="mb-4 p-4 bg-cyan-50 rounded-lg">
              <p class="font-semibold text-cyan-800">
                Critical: Discharge must be 6-10 feet from foundation minimum
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
              <div>
                <h5 class="font-semibold mb-2">Trench Requirements</h5>
                <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
                  <li>• <strong>Depth:</strong> 12-18 inches (below frost)</li>
                  <li>• <strong>Width:</strong> 6 inches minimum</li>
                  <li>• <strong>Slope:</strong> 1/8" per foot away</li>
                  <li>• <strong>Length:</strong> 10 feet minimum</li>
                  <li>• <strong>Endpoint:</strong> Daylight or dry well</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              
              <div>
                <h5 class="font-semibold mb-2">Pipe Assembly</h5>
                <ol class="text-sm space-y-1">
                  <li>1. Install check valve above pump</li>
                  <li>2. Add union fitting for service</li>
                  <li>3. Run 1-1/2" ABS to exterior</li>
                  <li>4. Install freeze relief hole (1/8")</li>
                  <li>5. Exit through rim joist or wall</li>
                </ol>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="mt-4 p-3 bg-amber-50 rounded-lg">
              <p class="text-sm">
                <strong>Freeze Protection:</strong> Drill 1/8" relief hole in discharge pipe inside basement, 6" above pump. This prevents freezing in winter.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Step 3: Gluing Black ABS Pipe -->
          <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-6 mb-4">
            <h4 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-orange-700">Step 3: Gluing Black ABS Pipe</h4>
            
            <div class="bg-orange-100 rounded-lg p-4 mb-4">
              <p class="font-semibold text-orange-900">
                ⚠️ Yellow ABS Cement ONLY - Sets in 30 seconds!
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="space-y-3">
              <div class="flex items-start">
                <span class="bg-orange-600 text-white rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-3 flex-shrink-0">1</span>
                <div>
                  <strong>Cut pipe square</strong>
                  <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">Use ABS pipe cutter or fine-tooth saw</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-start">
                <span class="bg-orange-600 text-white rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-3 flex-shrink-0">2</span>
                <div>
                  <strong>Deburr edges</strong>
                  <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">Remove all burrs with knife or sandpaper</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-start">
                <span class="bg-orange-600 text-white rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-3 flex-shrink-0">3</span>
                <div>
                  <strong>Dry fit first</strong>
                  <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">Mark alignment with pencil</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-start">
                <span class="bg-orange-600 text-white rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-3 flex-shrink-0">4</span>
                <div>
                  <strong>Apply cement to fitting first</strong>
                  <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">Coat socket completely</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-start">
                <span class="bg-orange-600 text-white rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-3 flex-shrink-0">5</span>
                <div>
                  <strong>Apply cement to pipe</strong>
                  <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">Cover insertion depth</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-start">
                <span class="bg-orange-600 text-white rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-3 flex-shrink-0">6</span>
                <div>
                  <strong>Push together with 1/4 turn</strong>
                  <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">Hold for 30 seconds</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Concrete Mixing Guide -->
        <div class="bg-cyan-50 rounded-lg p-8 mb-8">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Concrete Mixing for Sump Pit</h3>
          
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold mb-4">Concrete Mix Recipe</h4>
              
              <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-4 mb-4">
                <h5 class="font-semibold mb-2">For 4" Slab Around Pit</h5>
                <ul class="text-sm space-y-2">
                  <li>• <strong>Mix:</strong> 3,000 PSI (20 MPa)</li>
                  <li>• <strong>Ratio:</strong> 1:2:3 (cement:sand:gravel)</li>
                  <li>• <strong>Bags needed:</strong> 3-4 (60 lb bags)</li>
                  <li>• <strong>Water ratio:</strong> 0.5 (half weight of cement)</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              
              <div class="bg-amber-50 rounded-lg p-4">
                <h5 class="font-semibold mb-2">Water Guidelines</h5>
                <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
                  <li>• 60 lb bag = 0.5 gallons water</li>
                  <li>• 80 lb bag = 0.6 gallons water</li>
                  <li>• Less water = stronger concrete</li>
                  <li>• Consistency: thick oatmeal</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold mb-4">Mixing Instructions</h4>
              
              <div class="space-y-3">
                <div class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="bg-cyan-600 text-white rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-3 flex-shrink-0">1</span>
                  <div>
                    <strong>Add 2/3 water to mixer</strong>
                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">Or wheelbarrow for hand mixing</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="bg-cyan-600 text-white rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-3 flex-shrink-0">2</span>
                  <div>
                    <strong>Add dry mix gradually</strong>
                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">Avoid dust clouds</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="bg-cyan-600 text-white rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-3 flex-shrink-0">3</span>
                  <div>
                    <strong>Mix 3-5 minutes</strong>
                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">Until uniform color</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="bg-cyan-600 text-white rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-3 flex-shrink-0">4</span>
                  <div>
                    <strong>Add remaining water slowly</strong>
                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">Stop when consistency is right</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="bg-cyan-600 text-white rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-3 flex-shrink-0">5</span>
                  <div>
                    <strong>Slump test</strong>
                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">Should hold shape but settle slowly</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              
              <div class="mt-4 p-3 bg-red-100 rounded-lg">
                <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-red-700">
                  Never add water after initial mixing - ruins strength!
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="mt-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-lg p-4">
            <h5 class="font-bold mb-2">Finishing the Slab</h5>
            <ol class="text-sm space-y-1">
              <li>1. Pour concrete around basin, not under it</li>
              <li>2. Level with straight edge</li>
              <li>3. Float surface smooth</li>
              <li>4. Slope slightly toward pit (1/8" per foot)</li>
              <li>5. Cover with plastic for 48 hours</li>
              <li>6. Keep moist for 7 days for full strength</li>
            </ol>
          </div>
        </div>

